Last Saturday @glamourmag and the @vp co-hosted a Women’s History Month brunch with 80 trailblazers. Vice President Harris talked about women’s power, economic empowerment, and the importance of passing paid leave. One of Glamour’s paid leave mothers Karina Garcia @cocinaconsuelonyc talked about the project and her commitment to telling her story and changing the law. 

I spoke about Glamour’s storied history in fighting for women, Glamour’s celebration of women with Women of the Year, and the title’s commitment to advocating for the future of women in the US.

Huge thank you to the @glamourmag and @vp team that pulled it all together in less than two weeks!

Tomorrow we will come together to celebrate your life but it is still inconceivable that you are gone @edwardo71. Your lucky friends will forever be changed by your kindness and joy. I’d heard about Irish Eddie for weeks before meeting you outside a Halloween party in 2014. From that first moment you showed me nothing but love, regaling me with your stories of your own move from Ireland to New York, and generously introducing me to your nearest and dearest. You inspired me to never, ever lose enthusiasm & delight in everything we got to experience together- whether that was a walk in the west village, a 530pm dinner or a fabulous fashion event. The boy from castleisland, who arrived in NYC in 1990 with two pairs of pants and one jumper, made a permanent mark on this city and the hearts of everyone you knew. We love you and miss you terribly.

Our special cover and package on #bridesmaidburnout is live. Run to the site to see everything from @ru_wolle personal resignation letter to @han.worldwide insight on how bridesmaid have been treated through history. @stephemcneal unearths some bridemaids confessionals that will make you gasp , @jenny.leah.singer tackles how to just say no to being a bridesmaids (or say no with conditions) and @perriesamotin tackles the financial strain and what brides should pay for (everything?).

A huge shoutout to the whole @glamourmag team behind this special issue, especially @ru_wolle for starting the whole project, @perriesamotin for her brilliant direction, @alliefolino @hall.kathryne and photographer @_hannahwhitaker for bringing the vision to life..

Some #nyfw outfits with a splash of #usopen 

Thanks to @ig.arthur for some of the best shots. I’ve tagged some outfit details for those asking….including a tale of two red dresses, one investment @maisonalaia i bought for my first day @glamourmag and the other a recent @zara purchase.

Not included: the emotional costs of #BridesmaidBurnout.

It’s unclear when the job of being a bridesmaid went from being mildly annoying to being precipitously, obscenely, recklessly off the rails. We’re tired, hungover, broke, and itchy (see chiffon), and we believe it’s time to reassess long-held beliefs about what it means to be a good friend and act in our own self-interest while keeping meaningful relationships intact.

For this special issue of @glamourmag, you’ll find practical advice (how to say no to being a bridesmaid without fracturing your relationships, how to be a considerate bride, how to ask up front about what your commitment will cost), unique perspectives (why one editor is resigning from being a bridesmaid having only performed the role three times, and why another believes brides should be footing all the bills), relatable tales (anonymous bridesmaid horror stories), and some cute and affordable dresses to consider if you’re not ready to hang up your (metallic) bridesmaid heels for good. Read it all at the link in bio.

I’m thrilled to welcome @sambarry Editor-in-Chief of @glamourmag as my guest on the pod this week 🚀 ✨ 

Born and raised in Cork, Ireland, Samantha became the first editor-in-chief of a Conde Nast publication to have never previously worked in print media when she was appointed editor-in-chief by Anna Wintour. Under her leadership, Glamour has reached record breaking monthly audiences and grown their video content hugely with Barry recently interviewing the US First Lady, Dr Jill Biden. Prior to joining Glamour Barry served as executive producer for social and emerging media at CNN Worldwide. Under her leadership at CNN, the network became the most followed news organization in the world.
  
In this conversation we talked about her incredible career, imposter syndrome, being an immigrant & putting down roots in New York and getting her start on late night news reading shifts in RTE. Samantha is a leading light in global media and I couldn’t be more thrilled that she’s chatted to me on The Number.

#glamourmagazine #numbers #podcast #impostersyndrome #womenempowerment #femaleleaders #womeninmedia
